## Tips for SME Owners Getting Vehicle Financing

After 40 years in this business, we've learned a few things:

### 1. Match Tenure to Vehicle Life

Don't finance a vehicle over 7 years if you expect to replace it in 4. You'll end up paying for something you're not using.

### 2. Consider Total Cost of Ownership

The monthly payment is just part of it. Factor in:
- Road tax and insurance
- Fuel costs
- Maintenance and servicing
- Driver wages (if applicable)

### 3. Don't Overstretch

Yes, that brand-new Hino is attractive. But if a reliable used lorry does the job, you'll sleep better with lower monthly payments.

### 4. Keep Business and Personal Separate

Use a dedicated business account. It makes documentation cleaner and shows financiers you're organized.

### 5. Plan for Seasonality

If your business has slow months (like many do after CNY), factor that into your payment schedule discussions.

